original: Hainer, Elsa, advokat, Borås, f. 23/ 8/04 i Skara av läroviadj. Otto H. o. Anna Fagerholm. — Stud:ex. v. Sthilms lyc. f. fl. 24, jur. kand. i Sthlm 29. Tingstjg. i Västerbergslags doms. 29-32, bitr. jur. å Gunnar Fogelqvists Advibyrå i Sundsvall 32-34, egen adv:-verksamh. i Borås 34-40, hitr. jur. å Erik Grenfors Adv:byrå i Borås 40-44, dito å Älvsb. 1. s. rättshjälpsanst. i Borås sed. 45. Led. av Sv:es adv:-,samf. sed. 34.
translated: Hainer, Elsa, lawyer, Borås, born August 23rd, 1904 in Skara to teacher assistant Otto H. and Anna Fagerholm. Completed high school at Stockholm's high school in several years starting from age 24, earned a law degree in Stockholm in 1929. Served as district court judge in Västerbergslag from 1929 to 1932, assistant lawyer at Gunnar Fogelqvist's law firm in Sundsvall from 1932 to 1934, owned her own law firm in Borås from 1934 to 1940, local lawyer at Erik Grenfors' law firm in Borås from 1940 to 1944, and has been a local lawyer at Älvsborg County's legal aid office in Borås since 1945. Elsa has been a member of Swedish Bar Association since 1934.
